elter_definition:
Latitude for the reference point [decimal number] of the STATION expressed in decimal degree [dec °] WGS84 using at least 6-digits after the decimal separator. Note: The definition of the reference point depends on the STYPE:
• PT (single/multiple point): is the location of the point itself;
• AREA (areal plot): is the centroid of the area;
• VLN (vertical profile): is the starting point of the vertical profile
• HLN (horizontal transect): is the starting point of the horizontal transect.

